 climate and cyclones to reductions in Arctic sea ice (1995) J. Geophys. Res., 100, pp. 4791-4806; Mysak, L.A., Manak, D.K., Arctic sea ice extent and anomalies, 1953-1984 (1989) Atmos.-Ocean, 27, pp. 376-405; Mysak, L.A., Venegas, S.A., Decadal climate oscillations in the Arctic: A new feedback loop for atmosphere-ice-ocean interactions (1998) Geophys. Res. Lett., 25, pp. 3607-3610; Mysak, L.A., Manak, D.K., Marsden, R.E., Sea-ice anomalies in the Greenland and Labrador Seas during 1901-1984 and their relation to an interdecadal Arctic climate cycle (1990) Climate Dyn., 5, pp. 111-133; Mysak, L.A., Ingram, R.G., Wang, J., Baaren, A.V.D., The anomalous sea-ice extent in Hudson Bay, Baffin Bay and the Labrador Sea during three simultaneous ENSO and NAO episodes (1996) Atmos.-Ocean, 34, pp. 313-343; Newson, R.L., Response of a general circulation model of the atmosphere to the removal of the Arctic ice cap (1973) Nature, 241, pp. 39-40; Niebauer, H.J., Effects of El Nin̄o-Southern Oscillation and North Pacific weather patterns on interannual variability in the southern Bering Sea (1988) J. Geophys. Res., 93, pp. 5051-5068; Overland, J.E., Pease, C.H., Cyclone climatology of the Bering Sea and its relation to cyclone extent (1982) Mon. Wea. Rev., 110, pp. 5-13; Parkinson, C.L., Cavalieri, D.J., Gloersen, P., Zwally, H.J., Comiso, J., Arctic sea ice extents, areas and trends, 1978-1996 (1999) J. Geophys. Res., 104, pp. 20837-20856; Parkinson, C.L., Rind, D., Healy, R.J., Martinson, D.C., The impact of sea ice concentration on climate model simulations with the GISS GCM (2001) J. Climate, 14, pp. 2606-2623; Peng, S., Whitaker, L.S., Mechanisms determining the atmospheric response to midlatitude SST anomalies (1999) J. Climate, 12, pp. 1393-1408; Peng, S., Robinson, W.A., Relationships between atmospheric internal variability and the responses to an extratropical SST anomaly (2001) J. Climate, 14, pp. 2943-2959; Polyakov, I.V., Johnson, M.A., Arctic decadal and interdecad