land, C., Changes of probability associated with El Nin̄o (2000) J. Climate, 13, pp. 4268-4286; Scott, J.D., Alexander, M.A., Timlin, M.S., Bhatt, U.S., Miller, J., Walsh, J.E., (2003) CCM3 Sea Ice Forcing Experiments: Boundary Conditions and Response in Winter, , http://www.cdc.noaa.gov/~jds/lce, cited [Available online at]; Serreze, M.C., Carse, F., Barry, R.G., Kogers, J.C., Icelandic low cyclone activity: Climatological features, linkages with the NAO, and relationships with recent changes in the Northern Hemisphere circulation (1997) J. Climate, 10, pp. 453-464; Serreze, M.C., Observational evidence of recent change in the northern high-latitude environment (2000) Climatic Change, 46, pp. 159-207. , Coauthors; Simmonds, I., Budd, W.F., Sensitivity of the Southern Hemisphere circulation to leads in the Antarctic pack ice (1991) Quart. J. Roy. Meteor. Soc., 117, pp. 1003-1024; Slonosky, V.C., Mysak, L.A., Derome, J., Linking Arctic sea ice and atmospheric circulation anomalies on interannual and decadal timescales (1997) Atmos.-Ocean, 35, pp. 333-366; Walsh, J.E., Role of sea ice in climate variability: Theories and evidence (1983) Atmos.-Ocean, 21, pp. 229-242; Walsh, J.E., Johnson, C.M., An analysis of Arctic sea ice fluctuations, 1953-77 (1979) J. Phys. Oceanogr., 9, pp. 580-591; Walsh, J.E., Chapman, W.L., Arctic contribution to upper-ocean variability in the North Atlantic (1990) J. Climate, 3, pp. 1462-1473; Warshaw, M., Rapp, R.R., An experiment on the sensitivity of a global acidulation model (1973) J. Appl. Meteor., 12, pp. 43-49; Weatherly, J.W., Briegleb, B.P., Large, W.G., Maslanik, J.A., Sea ice and polar climate in the NCAR CSM (1998) J. Climate, 11, pp. 1472-1486; Williams, J., Barry, R.G., Washington, W., Simulation of the atmospheric circulation using the NCAR global circulation model with ice age boundary conditions (1974) J. Appl. Meteor., 13, pp. 305-317","Alexander, M.; NOAA-CIRES Climate Diagnostics Ctr., R/CDCI, 325 Broadway, Boulder, CO 80